{"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Some components can be used for ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"layouts","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"text":"Colored Surface","anchor":"Colored-Surface","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Orange"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_OrangeCompact"}]}],"title":"Orange Compact"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Sosh"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Wireframe"}]}],"title":"Wireframe"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mono"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" suffix (for instance "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"colorBgDefaultEnabledMono"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider"}]},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"anchor":"How-it-works","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"How it works"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the color, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"oudsUseMonochrome","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"oudsOnColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"How-to-use","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"How to use"},{"code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"onStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.onStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .foregroundColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .foregroundColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .coloredSurface(theme.colorModes.onStatusPositiveEmphasized)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Debuging contrast ratios"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", also named “RGAA”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components like "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can be used on "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratio.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratio.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"text":"Divider","type":"heading","anchor":"Divider"},{"level":4,"text":"How it works","type":"heading","anchor":"How-it-works"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSHorizontalDivider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":": to separate elements stacked vertically (e.g. in ","type":"text"},{"code":"VStack","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSVerticalDivider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked horizontally (e.g. in `HStack)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSDividerColor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":5,"anchor":"Horizontal","text":"Horizontal"},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Orange"}]}]},{"title":"Orange Compact","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_OrangeCompact","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Sosh","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Sosh","type":"image"}]}]},{"title":"Wireframe","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Wireframe"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":5,"anchor":"Vertical","text":"Vertical"},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Orange"}]}]},{"title":"Orange Compact","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_OrangeCompact"}]}]},{"title":"Sosh","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Sosh"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Wireframe","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":4,"anchor":"How-to-use","text":"How to use"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello world!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello world!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Layouts","images":[{"identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png","type":"card"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts"},"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSHorizontalDivider":{"abstract":[{"text":"Divider is a UI element that allows to structure the content by visually separating the content zones.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Divider improves readability and content organization without introducing a stronger visual hierarchy like a heading or a container would.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A horizontal Divider is used to separate content laid out one under the other ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VStack"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The divider can be colored using dedicated "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSDividerColor"},{"type":"text","text":" colors."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The thickness (height) is fixed by dedicated token from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTheme"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSHorizontalDivider","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudshorizontaldivider","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSHorizontalDivider","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"t